# Cursor Backend-Only Mode Rules

## CRITICAL: Backend-Only Enforcement

You are ONLY allowed to modify backend code. You may NOT modify any front-end, UI, components, pages, or client-side files.

## Forbidden Paths

Any file path starting with these prefixes is FORBIDDEN:
- `/src`
- `/app`
- `/components`
- `/pages`
- `/public`
- `/ui`
- `/styles`
- `/assets`

## Allowed Paths

You may ONLY modify files in:
- `/backend/**`
- `/imo_creator/**`
- `/config/**`
- `/ctb/**`
- `/tests/**` (backend tests only)

## Enforcement

Before applying ANY code change:
1. Check if file_path starts with any forbidden path
2. If YES: REJECT with message "Front-end modification is not allowed. Backend-only mode is active."
3. If NO: Proceed with change

## Allowed Tasks

✅ Backend API endpoints
✅ Database migrations
✅ Scoring/saturation logic
✅ Service integrations
✅ Pipeline steps
✅ Process registry
✅ Global config
✅ Async functions
✅ Error handlers
✅ Logging
✅ Tests

## Forbidden Tasks

❌ React components
❌ TypeScript UI
❌ Tailwind CSS
❌ Client-side code
❌ UI components
❌ Frontend routing
❌ Client services

## Context

- Backend: FastAPI + asyncpg + Neon
- Frontend: Lovable.dev (OFF-LIMITS)
- Doctrine: CTB + Altitude + Global Config

